adGenAOSCpuUtilMib.name: adGenAOSCpuUtilMib

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.
Added resource utilization OIDs for traps and tables.
Added sysName to adGenAOSResUtilThreshAlarm and adGenAOSResUtilThreshNormal.

adGenAOSCpuUtilMib.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOSCpuUtilMib.description: This MIB contains information regarding CPU utilization, Memory usage and system process status.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshTraps.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshTraps
adGenAOSResUtilThreshTraps.description: These traps indicate that a resource's utilization status has changed respective of a set threshold value. There are two types of traps, Alarm and Normal. The traps will return the adGenAOSResUtilThreshTable indices and the number of seconds since epoch as a timestamp indicating when the utilization status changed. The timestamp value is indicative of when the utilization status changed an not when the trap was sent.

adGenAOSCurrentCpuUtil.name: adGenAOSCurrentCpuUtil
adGenAOSCurrentCpuUtil.description: Average CPU utilization over the last second.

adGenAOSClearUtilizationStats.name: adGenAOSClearUtilizationStats
adGenAOSClearUtilizationStats.description: Set value to 1 to clear CPU utilization statistics.

adGenAOS1MinCpuUtil.name: adGenAOS1MinCpuUtil
adGenAOS1MinCpuUtil.description: Average CPU utilization over the last minute.

adGenAOS5MinCpuUtil.name: adGenAOS5MinCpuUtil
adGenAOS5MinCpuUtil.description: Average CPU utilization over the last 5 minutes.

adGenAOSMaxCpuUtil.name: adGenAOSMaxCpuUtil
adGenAOSMaxCpuUtil.description: Maximum CPU utilization since last system reboot or statistics reset.

adGenAOSHeapSize.name: adGenAOSHeapSize
adGenAOSHeapSize.description: Total Heap size. This is the amount of memory available after the code is decompressed and packet buffers are allocated.

adGenAOSHeapFree.name: adGenAOSHeapFree
adGenAOSHeapFree.description: Current amount of heap available for use.

adGenAOSProcessTable.name: adGenAOSProcessTable
adGenAOSProcessTable.description: A table reporting the current run state of all current processes.

adGenAOSProcessEntry.name: adGenAOSProcessEntry
adGenAOSProcessEntry.description: Each entry in the list is a current system process.

adGenAOSProcCount.name: adGenAOSProcCount
adGenAOSProcCount.description: Current number of times the process has been invoked.

adGenAOSProcExecTime.name: adGenAOSProcExecTime
adGenAOSProcExecTime.description: Total amount of time spent executing this process. Result is in usec.

adGenAOSProcRunTime.name: adGenAOSProcRunTime
adGenAOSProcRunTime.description: Total amount of time spent executing this process. Result is in usec.

adGenAOSProc1SecLd.name: adGenAOSProc1SecLd
adGenAOSProc1SecLd.description: Percent system utilization for the process.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshTable.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshTable
adGenAOSResUtilThreshTable.description: A table reporting the current resource utilization threshold traps with abilities to configure the traps. The table supports create and destroy. To prevent abuse, the table will not support row creation once 20 or more entries exist within the table.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshEntry.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshEntry
adGenAOSResUtilThreshEntry.description: Each entry in the table represents a current resource utilization threshold notification. The entry is composed of an enumerated integer representing the resource type, the numerical threshold and time interval settings. All entries are immutable and all columns are required for create.

adGenAOSResType.name: adGenAOSResType
adGenAOSResType.description: Indentifier specifying the resource type. Resource notes: (2) Heap - The heap resource will only display a time interval value of 1. Setting the value to a valid time interval value will always result in the inherent default value of 1. A heap notification will occur whenever the threshold is exceeded.

adGenAOSResUtilThresh.name: adGenAOSResUtilThresh
adGenAOSResUtilThresh.description: The utilization threshold value expressed as a whole number percentage.

adGenAOSResUtilTimeInterval.name: adGenAOSResUtilTimeInterval
adGenAOSResUtilTimeInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for actual to exceed threshold.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshRowStatus.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshRowStatus
adGenAOSResUtilThreshRowStatus.description: RowStatus column for this table. Since each entry is immutable the only acceptable RowStatus values (for set) are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). The only acceptable RowStatus value for get is active(1).

adGenAOSResUtilThreshTimestamp.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshTimestamp
adGenAOSResUtilThreshTimestamp.description: The time (seconds since epoch) that a resource utilization threshold trap condition occurred and not necessarily the when the trap was sent.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshAlarm.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshAlarm
adGenAOSResUtilThreshAlarm.description: This trap indicates the resource utilization exceeded the set threshold value for the entirety of the set time interval. The specific resource utilization is specified via the indexes adGenAOSResType, adGenAOSResUtilThresh, and adGenAOSResUtilTimeInterval. The adGenAOSResUtilThreshTimestamp indicates when this condition occurred and not necessarily when the trap was sent. The sysName is the exact same as defined in SNMPv2-MIB.

adGenAOSResUtilThreshNormal.name: adGenAOSResUtilThreshNormal
adGenAOSResUtilThreshNormal.description: This trap indicates the resource utilization has been in a normal (non-alarm) state for at least 5 seconds. This condition can only occur after the alarm state has been triggered. The specific resource utilization is specified via the indexes adGenAOSResType, adGenAOSResUtilThresh, and adGenAOSResUtilTimeInterval. The adGenAOSResUtilThreshTimestamp indicates when this condition occurred and not necessarily when the trap was sent.The sysName is the exact same as defined in SNMPv2-MIB.

adAOSCompliance.name: adAOSCompliance
adAOSCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the adAosCPU.mib

adGenAOSProcessGroup.name: adGenAOSProcessGroup
adGenAOSProcessGroup.description: This group is used to report the status of current processes.

adGenAOSThresholdGroup.name: adGenAOSThresholdGroup
adGenAOSThresholdGroup.description: The threshold config group. Contains objects to set and get the threshold and time interval to trigger a trap.

adGenAOSThresholdTrapGroup.name: adGenAOSThresholdTrapGroup
adGenAOSThresholdTrapGroup.description: Traps which may be used to enhance event driven management of the CPU.
